
<purchabr>CHRYSLER</purchabr>, <acqabr>LAMBORGHINI</acqabr> STILL IN JOINT VENTURE TALKS
    BOLOGNA, Italy, March 24 - Joint venture talks that could
lead to <purchaser>Chrysler Corp</purchaser> {<purchcode>C</purchcode>} taking a stake in <acqloc>Italian</acqloc> <acqbus>car maker</acqbus>
{<acquired>Automobili Lamborghini SpA</acquired>} are continuing, a <acqabr>Lamborghini</acqabr>
spokesman said.
    He told Reuters the two companies are discussing a number
of topics ranging from "a joint venture in the production area
to <purchabr>Chrysler</purchabr> becoming a shareholding partner" in the Italian
firm.
    The spokesman declined to comment on whether <purchabr>Chrysler</purchabr> was
interested in acquiring control of <acqabr>Lamborghini</acqabr> or if the two
sides were close to an accord.
    He said the two companies are discussing the possibility of
