Market.
    The spokesman said <purchabr>Chrysler</purchabr> officials in Detroit had
already visited <acqabr>Lamborghini</acqabr>'s production plant in <acqloc>Bologna</acqloc> and
another visit may be scheduled.
    <acqabr>Lamborghini</acqabr>, which is controlled by the Mimran Group of
Switzerland, broke even last year on sales of 29 billion lire,
